article.headline: Campbell 106, NC Pembroke 66
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Russ Gibson scored 22 points and Jake Wohlfeil added 20 off the bench to lift Campbell to a 106-66 rout of North Carolina-Pembroke on Saturday. Eric Smith had 14 points while freshman Jonathan Rodriguez posted 13 points, eight rebounds and seven assists for the Camels (1-0). Ruell Pringle scored 10 and Ledell Eackles had seven assists and a school-record 10 steals in 21 minutes. Campbell's 21-0 run midway through the first half broke open the contest against the Division II Braves (0-1). The Camels shot 63.3 percent (38-60) from the field and made 21-of-29 from the line (.724). Freshman Jamelle Lowery led all Braves scorers with 18 points off the bench on 6-of-12 shooting. Sylvester Brooks added 12 for N.C.-Pembroke, which shot just 36.9 percent (24-65) for the game.
